vation through the Jackson Hope Fund  fully staffing the Chaplain s Office  a  90 million increase to the overall endowment  and nearly  1 million to conduct renovations of the Stonewall Jackson House and the Turman House  At last May s commencement ceremonies  I told the graduating cadets that while higher education institutions around the country can be demanding and challenging  a VMI education tests them on all levels and that VMI insures a  value based  education  I reminded them that they succeeded not only because of their determination and self discipline  but because they had been  helped  by so many others  Along with family  friends  faculty  coaches  and Brother Rats  that all of you in this room  this evening  had a major hand in their success  too  because of your incredible support  Thank you for your dedication and commitment and for taking a stand in support of OUR VMI  As I have often said   VMI is a  National Treasure  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Ac