ate resources that allow VMI to maintain a 11 1 cadet to faculty ratio also allows cadets like Tyler direct access to what I think are some of the best instructor  educators in the nation  LTC Tim Moore  97 Although he may not have known it then  donor support played a major role in causing LTC Moore to leave a successful engineering career to return to his alma mater to teach in 2010  Tim recognized at that time the effect that faculty can have on cadets  and he was willing to make the  career change  because of people in this room who have invested in faculty support and academic innovation  With your support  Tim was able to create the  Field to Forum  program  an interdisciplinary program that helps cadets bridge the gap between the classroom and the world of practice as professional engineers  He also created the VMI Clean Energy and Air Resources Program  known as CLEAR  that is noted for developing sustainable bio fuels  The CLEAR Program   with your generous contributions for academic research   gives cadets opportunities to study and create clean burning bio fuels from soybeans  And Tim didn t stop there   he also founded the service group  Keydets Without Borders  Under this program  dozens of cadets have traveled to the mountain village of Pampoyo  in Bolivia  and not only installed a safe water system but also began a project to bring indoor plumbing to each family in the village  If you have supported this group  you have helped make possible a significant drop in infant mortality in Pampoyo  Colonel Moore was the State Council of Higher Education in Virginia s Outstanding Faculty Rising Star  Recipient this year  It is no wonder that cadets have said   I know I can make a difference in the world now  and Colonel Moore was the one who helped me see that  COL Jim Turner  65 After a successful career in biomedical research  medical education  and administration  Jim returned to VMI full time in 2001  He has served as VMI s founding director of undergraduate research  he has chaired the Biology Department since 2009  and in 2013 he became the founding chair of the VMI Service Committee  Donor contributions created the Beverly M  Read  41 Institute Professorship in the Arts and Sciences  and Jim s service has been recognized by naming him to this professorship  The Jackson Hope Fund and other academic resources made possible by donors have enabled Jim to engage in transformative mentoring of cadets through his teaching and research interests  He is one of the few VMI alumni or faculty who are two time recipients of the Virginia Military Institute Achievement Medal for exceptional service  He received the State Council of Higher Education in Virginia s  Outstanding Faculty  Award this year  and your generosity has played a key role in the work he has done to earn this prestigious honor  Please join me in acknowledging the fine work of these  representative  members of the VMI community and recipients of your generous donations  There are many other achievements of the campaign to date  that could be mentioned  including the establishment of four new professorships  173 new scholarships  73 athletic  gifts and commitments of  6 7 million for research and innovation through the Jackson Hope Fund  fully staffing the Chaplain s Office  a  90 million increase to the overall endowment  and nearly  1 million to conduct renovations of the Stonewall Jackson House and the Turman House  At last May s commencement ceremonies  I told the graduating cadets that while higher education institutions around the country can be demanding and challenging  a VMI education tests them on all levels and that VMI insures a  value based  education  I reminded them that they succeeded not only because of their determination and self discipline  but because they had been  helped  by so many others  Along with family  friends  faculty  coaches  and Brother Rats  that all of you in this room  this evening  had a major hand in their success  too  because of your incredible support  Thank you for your dedication and commitment and for taking a stand in support of OUR VMI  As I have often said   VMI is a  National Treasure                                               VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni VMI Foundation VMI Foundation Keydet Club Keydet Club Alumni Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Webcams Webcams Directories Directories My VMI My VMI RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity RESOURCES RESOURCES Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy Title IX  Health   Safety IT Site Index  Parents   Families Cadets Non discrimination Statement Privacy THE VMI PHILOSOPHY  THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lex